Chilean army chief and former president General  Augusto Pinochet arrived in Prague Monday, where he is expected to discuss  possible arms deals, CTK agency said.
CTK said he arrived by road from Amsterdam for a private visit of several  days on the invitation of Omnipol, a company specialising in arms exports.
Diplomatic sources quoted by CTK said Pinochet would be discussing the  possible purchase of armoured vehicles.
He is expected to remain in the country until June 4 and visit an arms and  military equipment show, IDET, opening on Wednesday in Brno.
